{
  "text": "An in vivo study [CITATION_1] found that the induction of vascular injury, involving a prominent role of growth factors, was associated with reduced levels of PKG. Moreover, in human arteries, neointimal areas express lower levels of PKG [CITATION_2] . Similarly, treatment with NO donors in vivo is associated with reduced PKG levels [CITATION_3] . Furthermore, a long-standing clinical problem is related to the resistance to NO that develops with the chronic use of nitroglycerin or other nitrovasodilators [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . PTP1B, originally discovered as a phosphatase that targets the insulin signaling pathway, is now known to target a variety of other proteins involved in intracellular signaling.",
  "correct_citation": {
